to provide intelligence data to the United States\' senior policy makers, the Intelligence Community and Department of Defense. More than half of Atlas V", "score": 0.60386235, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://www.hie.co.uk/media/10475/space-launch-market-analysis-2021.pdf", "title": "Space Launch Market Analysis", "content": "kg Estimated launch price $30 \\u2013 400 M Payload to LEO 500 \\u2013 4,000 kg Estimated launch price $5 \\u2013 50 M Payload to LEO <= 500 kg Estimated launch price $1 \\u2013 10 M Operational Rocket examples Rocket classification by payload capacity to LEO Target market Emerging market, with around 100 projects under development 12 North America China Other Asian countries Europe South America Australia 0% 25% 50% 75% 100% Ca. 100 projects globally announced to be developing a launcher to address the SmallSat", "score": 0.57322514, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://blog.ulalaunch.com/blog/nrol-101-payload-mounted-atop-atlas-v-for-launch", "title": "NROL-101: Payload mounted atop Atlas V for launch", "content": "The encapsulated payload was delivered to the Vertical Integration Facility (VIF) at Cape Canaveral Air Force Station today. ULA\'s payload transport vehicle positioned its cargo beneath the VIF crane that hoisted NROL-101 through the doorway and atop the Atlas V.  \\n  \\nThe completed launch vehicle now stands 206 feet (63 meters) tall. Once fully fueled during the countdown, Atlas V will weigh nearly one million pounds (453,600 kg).", "score": 0.5489884, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://blog.ulalaunch.com/blog/kuiper-2-atlas-v-to-launch-amazons-next-step-in-journey", "title": "Kuiper 2: Atlas V to launch Amazon\'s next step in journey", "content": "Atlas V will use five side-mounted solid rocket boosters to launch Kuiper 2. Photo by United Launch Alliance  \\n  \\nAtlas V stands 205 feet (62.5 m) tall, will weigh 1.3 million pounds (589,000 kg) once fueled for launch and lifts off on a combined thrust of 2.7 million pounds (12 megaNewtons) from its main engine and five SRBs.", "score": 0.40782914, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://newspaceeconomy.ca/2025/12/12/the-heavy-lifters-a-comparative-analysis-of-launch-vehicle-payload-capacities", "title": "The Heavy Lifters: A Comparative Analysis of Launch Vehicle Payload Capacities - New Space Economy", "content": "had a payload capacity of 28.7 metric tons to LEO. Vulcan Centaur is the new heavy-lift launch vehicle from United Launch Alliance, replacing both the Atlas V and Delta IV families. Long March 5B is a variant of China\\u2019s heavy-lift Long March 5 rocket, optimized for launching massive LEO modules like the Tiangong space station components. The Ariane 64 configuration (with four solid rocket boosters) has a payload capacity of 21.6 metric tons to LEO. The Saturn I was the first operational launch", "score": 0.38186535, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://www.facebook.com/ulalaunch/videos/atlas-v-highlight-reel-launching-amazon-leo-4/1192820565677110", "title": "6.1K views \\u00b7 3.3K reactions | Atlas V Highlight Reel: Launching Amazon Leo 4 | United Launch Alliance", "content": "Launch Alliance announces the arrival of our Atlas V rocket at its Cape Canaveral pad to launch Amazon Leo 5, currently planned for Sunday at 3:53 a.m. EDT (0753 UTC). ULA will deliver 29 satellites into orbit for this fifth Amazon Leo mission, marking the largest and heaviest payload ever for the venerable rocket. \\ud83c\\udfa5 Preparing Atlas V for Amazon Leo 5 Learn about the process ULA follows to prepare the 20-story-tall, 1.3-million-pound Atlas V 551 rocket to carry 29 broadband satellites into low", "score": 0.3637152, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://www.quora.com/How-much-does-it-cost-to-launch-rockets-by-Space-X-in-LEO-Low-Earth-Orbit-per-kgs-of-payload-capacity", "title": "How much does it cost to launch rockets by Space X in LEO (Low Earth Orbit) per kgs of payload capacity? - Quora", "content": "How much does it cost to launch rockets by Space X in LEO (Low Earth Orbit) per kgs of payload capacity? What is the current estimated cost per kg for launching a payload on SpaceX\'s Super Heavy/Starship system? How much does it cost to launch one ton of payload into space using SpaceX\'s Falcon 9 rocket? A dedicated Falcon 9 launch these days would cost $67 M, but that would let you launch maybe 16 to 18 tonnes to various low Earth orbits. How much does a SpaceX rocket cost per launch? How much", "score": 0.36046708, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://payloadspace.com/underutilized-capacity-on-dedicated-customer-falcon-9-rides-payload-research", "title": "Underutilized Capacity on Dedicated Customer Falcon 9 Rides: Payload Research", "content": "# Underutilized Capacity on Dedicated Customer Falcon 9 Rides: Payload Research\\n\\nJack KuhrJack Kuhr\\n\\nShare\\n\\n Twitter\\n Linkedin\\n Facebook\\n Email\\n\\nSpaceX has pushed up average payload mass for Falcon 9 Starlink-dedicated launches to roughly 16,850 kg, or 96% of max capacity of 17.5 tons to LEO in a reusable configuration, maximizing every meter and kilogram offered by the rocket.\\n\\nHowever, most customers don\\u2019t need all that capacity to LEO.", "score": 0.2602254, "raw_content": null}]',
